27/02/2007
BELGRADE, Serbia -- OSCE Chairman-in-Office, Spanish Foreign Minister Miguel Angel Moratinos, called for a solution to Kosovo that would be acceptable to both sides, during a meeting with Serbian Foreign Minister Vuk Draskovic in Belgrade on Monday (February 26th). 
He said that the OSCE would do everything possible to contribute to stability in the region and help Serbia proceed on the road to the EU. 
After meeting Tuesday with other officials in Belgrade, Moratinos travels on to Pristina.
On Monday, the OSCE Mission in Kosovo condemned an early morning explosion, which damaged nine vehicles in the OSCE parking area in Peja/Pec. 
No injuries were reported.
In other news Monday, the Democratic Party and Democratic Party of Serbia announced that negotiations on forming a new government in Belgrade would begin this week. 
Talks would focus on the basic policies and principles on which the new cabinet should be formed, rather than personnel issues. 
(Blic - 27/02/07; Beta, RTS, Tanjug, KosovaLive - 26/02/07)
